header.gameNote: COX COMMUNICATIONS CLASSIC AT NORFOLK VA

article.headline: Monmouth 69, Arkansas State 67 (OT)
article.story: NORFOLK, Va. (AP) -- Dejan Delic hit a jumper with 15 seconds left to give Monmouth a 69-67 overtime win over Arkansas State Sunday in the third round of the Cox Communication Classic. Mike Shipman hit two free throws with 1 second left to send the game into overtime. Marques Alston had five of his 16 points during overtime. Whitney Coleman also had 16 for the Hawks (1-2), and Shipman added 12. Adrian Banks sank 6-of-9 from the three-point line and finished with 24 for Arkansas State (0-3). Isaac Wells had 17. The Indians were up by six with 11:56 left in the second half, but Coleman scored 10 during a 14-4 Monmouth run that put the Hawks up by four at 53-49 with 7:13 remaining. Two free throws by Wells tied it at 56 apiece with 2:35 left. Arkansas State went up by as many as four before Shipman hit a layup with 28 seconds left then sank the last-second free throws.
